{"key":"post-19967165","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19967165</id>\n<content>The bottom line is you can fruit in open air if you mist enough.&amp;nbsp; However, none of us have time for that so we use terrariums to hold in some moisture.&amp;nbsp; However, if we hold in too much, we impede fresh air exchange.&amp;nbsp; This is the tightrope a shotgun terrarium is designed to walk. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A bit of extra verm on top gives you a place to store some water for the cakes when you're going to be gone for a day or two.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be careful not to saturate your cakes or let them dry out.&amp;nbsp; That's the balancing act we as cultivators must learn, and it only comes with experience.&amp;nbsp; Every one of us either has or will fuck up a few grows until we get it down.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19967258</next>\n<prev>19967159</prev>\n<first>19960917</first>\n<last>20008539</last>\n<when>1399740018</when>\n<utime>05/10/14 07:40 PM</utime>\n</post>"}